ration to Israel and the United States. Current issues facing the academic study of Judaism are discussed, including the role of private foundations that seek inroads into the academy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aJudaism. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Religious Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438448633423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438448633/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles